<div id='root'>
  <div class='left'>
    <div class='eye'>The Core Innovation</div>
    <h1>Two hard problems.<br><em>Both automated.</em></h1>
    <p class='intro'>Two separate engineering challenges. First: reading 25 completely different client formats reliably &mdash; structured Excel, scanned paper, JPEG, PDF, each with its own layout and inconsistencies. Azure Document Intelligence handles that. Second, and harder still: filling in what&apos;s missing. Many timesheets arrive without start time, end time, or break duration. Today someone does that from memory using the employee&apos;s contract and collective agreement. The gap-fill agent does it automatically.</p>
    <div class='steps'>
      <div class='st'><div class='st-num'>1</div><div><div class='st-title'>Timesheet arrives with missing fields</div><div class='st-body'>A client sends hours worked but no start, end, or break time &mdash; common across many formats.</div></div></div>
      <div class='st'><div class='st-num'>2</div><div><div class='st-title'>Agent identifies the employee</div><div class='st-body'>Using the employee ID, it queries Recman via API and pulls the active job record.</div></div></div>
      <div class='st'><div class='st-num'>3</div><div><div class='st-title'>Agent reads the collective agreement</div><div class='st-body'>It finds the kollektivavtal tied to that job and the contracted standard hours &mdash; including OB addition rules.</div></div></div>
      <div class='st'><div class='st-num'>4</div><div><div class='st-title'>Agent infers the missing fields</div><div class='st-body'>Fills in start time, end time, and break duration using the agreement&apos;s rules. No human involved.</div></div></div>
      <div class='st'><div class='st-num'>5</div><div><div class='st-title'>Writes clean record to Recman</div><div class='st-body'>Complete validated entry written directly to Recman. Unresolvable cases go to a human review queue with all data pre-surfaced.</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class='right'>
    <div class='example-box'>
      <div class='eb-head'>
        <div class='eb-title'>Live example &mdash; what the agent does</div>
        <div class='eb-sub'>Timesheet arrives for employee ID 4821 with missing start/end/break</div>
      </div>
      <div class='eb-body'>
        <div class='eb-row'><div class='eb-icon'>📄</div><div><div class='eb-label'>What arrived</div><div class='eb-val'>Employee: Erik Lindqvist &middot; Hours: 8 &middot; Start: <span style='color:#c41a1a;'>missing</span> &middot; End: <span style='color:#c41a1a;'>missing</span> &middot; Break: <span style='color:#c41a1a;'>missing</span></div></div></div>
        <div class='eb-row'><div class='eb-icon'>🔍</div><div><div class='eb-label'>Agent queries Recman</div><div class='eb-val code'>GET /employees/4821/jobs?active=true<br>&rarr; Job: Lagerarbetare &middot; Agreement: Detaljhandelsavtalet<br>&rarr; Standard hours: 08:00&ndash;17:00 &middot; Break: 60 min</div></div></div>
        <div class='eb-row'><div class='eb-icon'>⚡</div><div><div class='eb-label'>Agent infers missing fields</div><div class='eb-val good'>Start: 08:00 &middot; End: 17:00 &middot; Break: 09:00&ndash;10:00<br>Basis: Detaljhandelsavtalet &middot; OB1 window cleared</div></div></div>
        <div class='eb-row'><div class='eb-icon'>✓</div><div><div class='eb-label'>Written to Recman</div><div class='eb-val good'>Complete record imported. Audit trail logged. No human involved.</div></div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class='queue'>
      <div class='queue-title'>When it cannot resolve</div>
      <div class='queue-body'>If the agent cannot confidently infer the missing data &mdash; for example, multiple active jobs under different agreements &mdash; the case goes to a human review queue with everything pre-surfaced. One decision, not fifteen manual lookups.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
</body></html>"></iframe>

